<p class="challenge_1" style="text-align:left;">I'm trying to get into a secure multinational system.</p>
I don't have any network access to this system, but eventually I managed to intrude the company's local building and sneak into its computer center, yet I didn't have the admin password to gain access.
<br /><br />
I went through their trash a few days ago and - amongst tons of paper - found a magnetic tape. Although lacking the proper tape drive, I was able to analyse a piece of it. I noticed the tape has about 800 bpi. Here is the part of data I obtained:
<p class="challenge_mono_1" style="text-align:center;">1100111 0110000 1000110<br />
0111111&nbsp;0100010&nbsp;1000110<br />
1000010&nbsp;1011100&nbsp;1000110<br />
1011000&nbsp;0111111&nbsp;0110010<br />
1000110&nbsp;1010001&nbsp;1000000<br />
1001110&nbsp;1011101&nbsp;1000000<br />
1110111&nbsp;0111001&nbsp;0100100<br />
1001110&nbsp;1000001&nbsp;0100111<br />
0110000&nbsp;1000001&nbsp;0110100</p>
Unfortunately I don't know what kind of encoding the tape uses. Can you help me to decode this?
</div>
